<P>Chapter 8--Re-education</P>

<P>&#9;Basic theme:  computers and the web are not going to eliminate the</P>
<P>world as we know it.  best solution is to use them to augment and improve what we have.</P>

<P>&#9;On Colleges and Universities</P>

<P>&#9;1.  Pressures for Change</P>
<P>&#9;&#9;a.  Changes in Student Body</P>
<P>&#9;&#9;&#9;from one school for four years</P>
<P>&#9;&#9;&#9;from all 18-22 year olds</P>
<P>&#9;&#9;b.  Changes in Competition for students</P>
<P>&#9;&#9;&#9;Open University in UK</P>
<P>&#9;&#9;&#9;University of Phoenix</P>
<P>&#9;&#9;&#9;Unplug and play</P>
<P>&#9;&#9;    Changes in Competition on research</P>
<P>&#9;&#9;&#9;people and money</P>
<P>&#9;&#9;&#9;PARC, Microsoft</P>
<P>&#9;&#9;c.  New Technologies</P>
<P>&#9;&#9;&#9;Do things differently</P>
<P>&#9;&#9;&#9;Do things more cheaply</P>

<P>&#9;</P>
